dmca.title: Calling Card Site Alleges DMCA Violations by Competitor Site
dmca.body:
03-08-2005
Attn: User Support, DMCA complaints
Recently I have faxed you guys a copyright infringement issue, and its details, and you guys have removed the copyright infringing web pages from your database, I have received the confirmation of the resolution of the issue through e-mail.

My website is www.zscomm.com and the copyright infringing website is www.prepaidtelecomhq.com.

I have recently did a query search on google.com regarding this website, to see what pages could have been left on the google database that this website www.prepaidtelecomhq.com has pages of, that are copied from the pages of www.zscomm.com, and I have found a quite a few pages still existing on your database, a couple hundred of them. I am giving my search details, my statement of good faith, the details of the copyright infringement and the web pages below.

The search I did on google.com was (site:www.prepaidtelecomhq.com) which shows me the list of pages the specific website has on google.com database. I have spent extensive hours - couple of days - to go through each and every single page that has copied the pages from my website www.zscomm.com

The list of web pages below are the additional web pages that I have found out (these pages listed below are not the pages that I have sent the request about initially last week, these are completely new page extensions that exist on your database, and thus the copyright infringing website (www.prepaidtelecomhq.com) has copied from my website (www.zscomm.com)

I will be glad if you guys can have a look at this issue and remove the pages listed below from your database. This website out of nowhere has given me additional work load and copied my pages for its own benefit, it also seems to me that the website www.prepaidtelecomhq.com is an affiliate website of another, in the country pages it directs the visitor to another website when the user follows buy phone card from our partner link.

I sincerely thank you for your previous efforts on this issue, and will be glad and thankful for your continuing efforts.

Statement and details of the issue:

I am the owner of www.zscomm.com and the webmaster of the website www.zscomm.com I have dedicated days and months of my time to create a website that sells phone cards to consumers online. The website has been in business for 3 years.
I recently have found out that another website has copied my "text" on hundreds of pages in my website and used my copyrighted text on his/her website.
The copyright infringing website is www.prepaidtelecomhq.com and the infringement occurs in its web pages. Please see the list of all the web pages that has copied my text from my web pages and posted them as his/her.
I have created individual pages for each of the country that exist in the world and each of these pages have explanatory text and the phone card rates to that specific country. Ex: www.zscomm.com/albania.htm shows the phone cards for Albania, and etc.

The infringing website www.prepaidtelecomhq.com also has created pages for each country.
On my country pages (ex:Albania.htm, Algeria.htm etc.) I use a special text that is uniform and explain the page details to the visitors.
The text on all of the country web pages is as follows:
Text1: "Check out the lowest calling cards rates and phone cards rates below. Click on the calling card name for more details and to purchase. We provide the rates of all of the phone cards to specific countries for convenience."
And
Text2: "ZS Comm is providing you the international prepaid phone cards to call to "country name", and "country name" calling cards. With more than 50 prepaid calling card online you will
be able to get the cheapest calling card rates to call "country name", with "country name" phone cards and "country name" calling cards, we provide the high quality online calling card rates with high quality long distance calls from USA. Please browse the table below for all of the prepaid
phone card rates to call "country name", and then click on the name of the international calling card to get more details, and buy. "
The infringing website www.prepaidtelecomhq.com has used the following texts that have been copied from my web pages on his/her web pages (country name extensions)

Text1: "Check out the lowest phone cards rates and calling card rates below. Click on the phone card name for more information. We provide the rates of all of the phone cards to specific countries."

And

Text2: "Prepaid Telecom HQ is dedicate to provide the largest collection of the international prepaid phone cards and prepaid calling card to call to Algeria. More than 500 prepaid phone card in our database, you will be able to get the cheapest phone card rates to call Algeria, with Algeria phone cards and Algeria calling cards, we offer the cheapest rates, price and quality long distance calls from USA. Please browse the phone cards below for the prepaid phone card rates to call Algeria, and then click on the name of the international calling card to get more details. "
As you can see clearly from the above information
Text 1 of my website has been copied almost without any changes directly to www.prepaidtelecomhq.com country pages. And on text2 you can see most of the sentences are identical.
Below I have listed all of the pages that show the copyright infringement that was done by the owner of www.prepaidtelecomhq.com webmaster/owner. The total list is about 18 pages, and consist of a few hundred individual pages. Contact information for www.prepaidtelecomhq.com on
their website is listed as support@prepaidtelecomhq.com. My contact information is listed at the end of my statement.
I would be glad if you guys can remove these pages from your search engine database as it is clearly a violation of copyright laws. Your quick action on this issue is highly appreciated.
I have a good faith belief that use of the copyrighted materials described above on the allegedly infringing webpages is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or the law.
I swear, under penalty of perjury consistent with United States Code Title 17, Section 512, that the information in the notification is accurate and that I am the copyright owner or am authorized to act on behalf of the owner of an exclusive right that is allegedly infringed.

My Address: [Private]
Plano, TX 75093

My e-mail: [Private]@zscomm.com or [Private]@rocketmail.com 
Signature: /[Private]/
